The 27-year old suspect fled the scene after the attack last weekend &amp; her son is reportedly in a stable condition in hospital. CAPE TOWN A mother will appear in the Khayelitsha Magistrates Court after she allegedly stabbed her two-year old son.The 27-year old suspect fled the scene after the attack last weekend.The toddler is reportedly in a stable condition in hospital.The police s Frederik van Wyk says the circumstances surrounding he incident are unclear. The investigations into the circumstances surrounding an attempted murder case where the mother allegedly stabbed a two-year-old boy in his neck led to the arrest of the 27-year-old suspect. Crime against women and children are high on the priority list of the Western Cape police and we ll not tolerate such acts of violence. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)